<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1437,290,964]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
Habitat. Infralittoral species, on coarse sand containing biogenic calcareous fragments and shell gravel with coralline deposits (
<bibRefCitation author="Ozturk, D. S. &amp; Engin, S." box="[362,612,866,894]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" pagination="142 - 150" refId="ref62441" refString="Ozturk, D. S. &amp; Engin, S. (2019) Taxonomic status of the Mediterranean-endemic goby Pomatoschistus adriaticus Miller, 1973 inferred with both morphological and genetic data. Zoology in the Middle East, 65, 142 - 150. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 09397140.2019.1580932" type="journal article" year="2019">Öztürk &amp; Engin 2019</bibRefCitation>
), sand at 
<quantity box="[717,802,866,892]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.1" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" unit="m" value="10.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="1.0">1–20 m</quantity>
depth (
<bibRefCitation author="Patzner, R. A." box="[885,1038,866,892]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" refId="ref62855" refString="Patzner, R. A. (2021) Gobiidae. Available from: http: // www. patzner. sbg. ac. at / Gobiidae / GobiidaeSpecies. htm (accessed 1 October 2021)" type="url" year="2021">Patzner 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1437,290,964]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
Geographic distribution. Mediterranean. Known from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[903,982,902,928]" name="France" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">France</collectingCountry>
, the Adriatic Sea and the Sea of Marmara (summarized by 
<bibRefCitation author="Patzner, R. A." box="[339,490,938,964]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" refId="ref62855" refString="Patzner, R. A. (2021) Gobiidae. Available from: http: // www. patzner. sbg. ac. at / Gobiidae / GobiidaeSpecies. htm (accessed 1 October 2021)" type="url" year="2021">Patzner 2021</bibRefCitation>
